body:
Rock Addul True, because anyone who thinks that God only makes positive situations is very naive, and doesn't know what faith is. Natural disasters happen all the time... everything has a reason. We may not clearly understand the reasons, but many times it's to teach those who survive that this is a part of life. Life is not about only the good things. Sometimes it's telling us to get closer to God, it teaches us how to truly be appreciative of all we have, it's the WAY we deal with these types of calamities that shapes us. Like they say, "Patience is not the ability to wait, it's how you act 'while' you're waiting." And that when a door closes to you, it's not that God doesn't want you to have what you WANT, it's that God knows what you need. And God may be protecting you from something unforeseen by you.
Many times the events that happen to us seem cruel or wrong.... but we know not. That's what faith and belief is all about. When someone is blessed with sudden wealth, for example, that doesn't necessarily mean it's a 'good' thing. God sees how you deal.... with this blessing. Do you remain humble? Do you become arrogant? Do you develop greedy characteristics or charitable ones. Faith is believing in what you cannot see... but you have faith in. And all humans are tested in some way... whether you think it's right or fair, whether it seems cruel, it's to test our faith.
The sun rises, and it sets. That is a lesson right there for those who understand. Life is up and down, left and right, good and bad, there's ease and hardship... nothing in our lives is meant to be perfect. But those who 'expect' it to be are the ones who need faith the most, only in my opinion. The seasons themselves are also lessons. Things change.... and sometimes come with difficulties.... but the storms subside, and whatever we're left with always has a positive side. We just have to know how to recognize it, learn from it, and thank God for the chance to evolve into a better human being. Have faith and take care!
